          "<h2 id=\"quick-quiz\">Quick quiz</h2>\n\n<p>Answer the three questions. There are hints to guide you to the correct answer.</p>\n\n<p>When you have answered each question, click on <strong>Check my answer</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>Have fun!</p>\n\n<form class=\"knowledge-quiz-question\">\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Question 1 of 3</legend>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__blurb\">\n      <p>In your project, the bus glides away using this code:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">when flag clicked \nwait [4] seconds\nglide [2] secs to x: [320] y: [-100]\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>When does the bus glide away?</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answers\">\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"1\" id=\"choice-1\" />\n<label for=\"choice-1\"><p>Immediately when you click on the green flag</p></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"2\" id=\"choice-2\" checked/>\n<label for=\"choice-2\"><p>Four seconds after you click on the green flag</p></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"3\" id=\"choice-3\" />\n<label for=\"choice-3\"><p>When you click on the bus</p></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"4\" id=\"choice-4\" />\n<label for=\"choice-4\"><p>Two seconds after you click on the green flag</p></label>\n</div>\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n  <ul class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback\">\n  <li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-1\">\n<p>The code blocks run in order, look at the blocks before the <code class=\"block3motion\">glide</code> block.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-2\">\n<p>Yes. After you click on the green flag, there is a four-second wait before the bus glides away.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-3\">\n<p>The bus does not have any code that runs <code class=\"block3events\">when this sprite clicked</code>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-4\">\n<p>The bus takes two seconds to glide away, but that is not how long it waits before it moves.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n  <input type=\"button\" name=\"Submit\" value=\"submit\" />\n</form>\n\n",
          "<form class=\"knowledge-quiz-question\">\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Question 2 of 3</legend>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__blurb\">\n      <p>When you <strong>drag a sprite</strong> to a new position on the Stage, which <strong>properties</strong> will be updated in the Sprite pane below the Stage?</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answers\">\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"1\" id=\"choice-1\" />\n<label for=\"choice-1\"><p>The <strong>direction</strong> of the sprite <img src=\"https://projects-static.raspberrypi.org/projects/catch-the-bus/f80d0ecf4432ce4301c0337c0367f75a5ea55662/en/images/direction.png\" alt=\"The direction property.\" /></p></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"2\" id=\"choice-2\" checked/>\n<label for=\"choice-2\"><p>The <strong>x and y coordinates</strong> of the sprite <img src=\"https://projects-static.raspberrypi.org/projects/catch-the-bus/f80d0ecf4432ce4301c0337c0367f75a5ea55662/en/images/coordinates.png\" alt=\"The x and y coordinate properties.\" /></p></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"3\" id=\"choice-3\" />\n<label for=\"choice-3\"><p>Whether the sprite will <strong>show or hide</strong> <img src=\"https://projects-static.raspberrypi.org/projects/catch-the-bus/f80d0ecf4432ce4301c0337c0367f75a5ea55662/en/images/visibility.png\" alt=\"The show property.\" /></p></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"4\" id=\"choice-4\" />\n<label for=\"choice-4\"><p>The <strong>size</strong> of the sprite <img src=\"https://projects-static.raspberrypi.org/projects/catch-the-bus/f80d0ecf4432ce4301c0337c0367f75a5ea55662/en/images/size.png\" alt=\"The size property.\" /></p></label>\n</div>\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n  <ul class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback\">\n  <li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-1\">\n<p>To change the direction of the sprite, you need to go to the <strong>Direction</strong> property and change it.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-2\">\n<p>When you drag a sprite to a new position, the <strong>x</strong> and <strong>y</strong> coordinates are automatically updated.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-3\">\n<p>Using the <strong>eye</strong> and <strong>crossed-out eye</strong> icons will make the sprite show or hide.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-4\">\n<p>To change the size of the sprite, you need to go to the <strong>Size</strong> property and change the number there.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n  <input type=\"button\" name=\"Submit\" value=\"submit\" />\n</form>\n\n",
          "<form class=\"knowledge-quiz-question\">\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Question 3 of 3</legend>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__blurb\">\n      <p>Which of these scripts uses a <strong>loop</strong> to animate the dog?</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://projects-static.raspberrypi.org/projects/catch-the-bus/f80d0ecf4432ce4301c0337c0367f75a5ea55662/en/images/dog-run.gif\" alt=\"An animation of a dog running from the left of the Stage to the right.\" /></p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answers\">\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"1\" id=\"choice-1\" checked/>\n<label for=\"choice-1\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">when flag clicked\nrepeat (5)\nmove (5) steps\nnext costume\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"2\" id=\"choice-2\" />\n<label for=\"choice-2\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">when flag clicked \nnext costume\nmove (5) steps\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"3\" id=\"choice-3\" />\n<label for=\"choice-3\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">when flag clicked\nnext costume\nmove (5) steps\nnext costume\nmove (5) steps\nnext costume\nmove (5) steps\nnext costume\nmove (5) steps\nnext costume\nmove (5) steps\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"4\" id=\"choice-4\" />\n<label for=\"choice-4\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">when this sprite clicked \nnext costume\nmove (5) steps\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n  <ul class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback\">\n  <li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-1\">\n<p>Yes! The <code class=\"block3control\">repeat</code> code block uses a loop to make the dog run.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-2\">\n<p>This code makes the dog move, but only once. There is no loop here, so the code does not repeat.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-3\">\n<p>This code makes the dog run, but it does not use a loop. Using a loop can often make your code shorter.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-4\">\n<p>There is no loop here, so the dog would only move once. To make the dog run, you would have to add a loop.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n  <input type=\"button\" name=\"Submit\" value=\"submit\" />\n</form>\n\n"
        ],
